The paper deals with digital image steganalysis, which involves the detection of image steganography. This falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) to destroy steganographic content without compromising the perceptual quality of the original image, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves testing the transfer learning capability of the proposed model, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
